---ARCHITECTURE---
project:            llmisland-mix-tooling
version:            0.3-rc5
last-verified:      2026-05-03
description:        Reference tooling for the LLM Island System.
                    A thin orchestrator (llmisland_tooling.py) dispatches
                    subcommands into the tooling/ package. Each subcommand
                    is its own module; standard library only.

propagation-status: idle
propagation-pending:
  - none

bootstrap-mode:     greenfield
bootstrap-date:     2026-05-03

scope:              tooling-only — the spec/docs portion of mix is NOT
                    islanded. Only the Python sources under tooling/ and
                    llmisland_tooling.py at the project root participate
                    in this mainland. See notes.md item 8 (locked).

layers:
  orchestration:    [llmisland_tooling.py]
  core:             [tooling/common.py, tooling/types.py]
  io:               []                       # rc6: stale.py, spec_router.py
  data:             []                       # rc7: propagation.py
  test:             []
  config:           []
  build:            []
  bridge:           []

load-order:
  - tooling/types.py         :: dataclasses; imported by orchestrator + subcommands
  - tooling/common.py        :: helpers; loaded by every subcommand module
  - tooling/__init__.py      :: package marker
  - llmisland_tooling.py     :: entrypoint; imports Report from tooling.types

architectural-rules:
  - AR-001: every subcommand lives in its own module under tooling/
    self-checkable: true
  - AR-002: every cmd_* function returns either an int exit code or
            a tooling.common.Report dataclass; the orchestrator
            handles all formatting
    self-checkable: true
  - AR-003: --json and --include-examples must be available on every
            subcommand via argparse parent parsers (no per-cmd
            duplication, no decorators)
    self-checkable: true
  - AR-004: zero external dependencies; standard library only.
            requirements.txt does not exist by design
    self-checkable: true
  - AR-005: each tooling/*.py file stays under 300 lines (CONTRIBUTING
            yellow line); split into helper modules if it grows past
    self-checkable: false (requires line-count check; future check-size tool)

---CONNECTIONS---

CONNECTION: llmisland_tooling.py -> tooling/types.py
  uses:         Report (dataclass returned by subcommands)
  why:          orchestrator's _emit dispatcher needs the Report type
                to format JSON or text output uniformly
  direction:    orchestration -> core
  strength:     critical
  break-impact: every subcommand's output formatting fails;
                --json mode produces invalid output
  cycle:        false

CONNECTION: tooling/common.py -> (rc6+) subcommand modules
  uses:         iter_islands, source_for_island, find_project_root,
                read_header_field, parse_last_verified
  why:          rc6+ subcommands consume the file-system + parsing
                helpers from common.py. The connection becomes
                concrete as each subcommand module lands.
  direction:    core -> io / data
  strength:     high
  break-impact: subcommand modules cannot scan islands or parse dates;
                check-stale, check-decay, validate would all fail
  cycle:        false
  dynamic:      true
  dynamic-note: edge endpoint expands as rc6+ adds subcommand modules
                (stale.py, spec_router.py, propagation.py, rules.py,
                validate.py). The mainland CONNECTIONS will be filled
                in concretely with each new module.

---CONTRACTS---

CONTRACT: subcommand-return-shape
  statement:    every cmd_* returns either an int exit code or a
                tooling.common.Report dataclass. No subcommand may
                return a bare dict or define its own result type.
  owned-by:     llmisland_tooling.py (dispatcher enforces at runtime)
  enforced-by:  none yet — manual review until validate.py (rc8) lands
  islands-bound:[llmisland_tooling.py, tooling/common.py]
  violation-consequence: dispatcher cannot uniformly format output;
                         silent breakage of --json output mode for
                         the offending subcommand
  fragility:    high (rationale: not enforced by Python's type system;
                                  trivial to violate by returning a
                                  bare dict)

CONTRACT: zero-dependency
  statement:    every import in tooling/ and llmisland_tooling.py
                resolves to the Python 3.10+ standard library.
                requirements.txt MUST NOT be created.
  owned-by:     project root
  enforced-by:  none yet — manual review
  islands-bound:[llmisland_tooling.py, tooling/common.py]
  violation-consequence: adopters who installed mix without pip cannot
                         run the tools; zero-friction install promise
                         broken
  fragility:    high (rationale: easy to import a third-party module
                                  by reflex; no boundary in code to
                                  catch it)

CONTRACT: shared-flags-via-parent
  statement:    --json and --include-examples are added once on the
                shared parent parser in build_parser. Subcommands
                attach via parents=[common]. Subcommands MUST NOT
                redefine these flags.
  owned-by:     llmisland_tooling.py (build_parser)
  enforced-by:  none yet — manual review
  islands-bound:[llmisland_tooling.py]
  violation-consequence: argparse argument-conflict error at startup;
                         OR (worse) silent override of dispatcher's
                         flag handling
  fragility:    medium (rationale: argparse fails loudly on
                                    conflict-add, so a violation is
                                    detectable; less fragile than the
                                    return-shape contract)

---ARCHITECTURE-MEMORY---

ACTIVE-CONSTRAINTS:
  - id: MAC-001
    constraint:  the orchestrator must not duplicate logic from
                 tooling/ modules — its only job is parser
                 construction and dispatch
    applies-to:  [llmisland_tooling.py]
    established: 2026-05-03
    evidence:    inferred-from-design (HD-001)

  - id: MAC-002
    constraint:  the spec docs (LLMISLAND_SPEC.md, SPEC/*, README.md,
                 etc.) are NOT islanded and do not appear in this
                 mainland. Only the Python tooling layer is in scope.
    applies-to:  [project root]
    established: 2026-05-03
    evidence:    inferred-from-notes.md (locked decision item 8)

HISTORICAL-DECISIONS:
  - id: MHD-001
    decision:  hybrid orchestrator + package, not single-file CLI
    reason:    file-size rule (~200 / ~300 / 400+) pushed toward a
               package; an LLM working on the tools wants one
               entrypoint so it does not have to navigate to find
               the right file. Hybrid satisfies both: thin
               orchestrator (one name to remember) + small modules
               (each under the size limit).
    date:      2026-04-27
    outcome:   in use as of v0.3-rc5; first rc with code in this layout
    evidence:  inferred-from-notes.md

  - id: MHD-002
    decision:  argparse parent parsers for --json, not decorators
    reason:    the tooling will be maintained by an LLM. Parent
               parsers are a pattern every LLM has seen thousands of
               times in its training corpus; custom decorator stacks
               for CLI flag inheritance are not. When two designs
               are functionally equivalent, the LLM-recognizable one
               wins. (Meta-principle from notes.md.)
    date:      2026-04-27
    outcome:   in use as of v0.3-rc5
    evidence:  inferred-from-tooling questions responses.md

  - id: MHD-003
    decision:  bootstrap-mode greenfield (not legacy)
    reason:    the tooling layer is authored fresh with islands from
               day one — that matches the greenfield definition.
               The spec/docs portion of mix predates this work, but
               this mainland's scope is the tooling layer only.
    date:      2026-05-03
    outcome:   stable; first islands in mix are tooling-side
    evidence:  inferred-from-notes.md

  - id: MHD-004
    decision:  propagation state in a separate .llmpropstts file,
               NOT in this mainland
    reason:    transient operational state should not pollute the
               architectural document. The mainland describes intent;
               .llmpropstts describes operations in flight. Auto-
               deletes when a cascade completes, so its presence
               itself is a strong honest signal.
    date:      2026-04-27
    outcome:   propagation-status field stays at "idle"; tooling/
               propagation.py (rc7) manages the .llmpropstts file
    evidence:  inferred-from-tooling questions responses.md

SUPERSEDED:
  - none yet
